🔐 SAML SSO Integration using Microsoft Entra ID
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates the implementation of Single Sign-On (SSO) using Microsoft Entra ID.
The goal was to simulate a real-world IAM scenario where an enterprise application is integrated with an Identity Provider using SAML.

🎯 Objectives
Integrate an application with Entra ID
Configure SSO using SAML
Implement access control using RBAC
Understand identity claims and authentication flow
Validate SSO behavior in a simulated environment
🧩 Architecture
User → Microsoft Entra ID → SAML Response → Application
⚙️ Implementation Steps
1️⃣ Application Creation
Created a custom enterprise application in Entra ID
Selected “Integrate any other application”
2️⃣ SSO Configuration
Configured SAML-based SSO
Defined:
Entity ID
Reply URL (ACS)
Sign-on URL
Used dummy values for simulation
3️⃣ Claims Mapping
Configured identity attributes:
user.displayname → Name
user.mail → Email
4️⃣ Access Control
Assigned users and groups to the application
Implemented Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
5️⃣ Certificate Handling
Reviewed SAML signing certificate
Understood its role in securing SAML responses
6️⃣ Testing
Triggered SSO login via Entra ID
Verified authentication flow
Observed expected failure at application endpoint (due to simulation)
🔍 Key Learnings
How SAML-based SSO works in enterprise environments
Difference between Identity Provider and Application roles
Importance of claims in identity transmission
How access control is enforced before authentication completes
Role of digital certificates in securing identity exchanges
⚠️ Note

This project uses a simulated application with dummy endpoints.
The SSO flow was successfully validated up to the Identity Provider stage, but full login could not complete due to the absence of a real application backend.
